<tr id="L318"><td><a href="#L318">318</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Inside, Miranda is performing a sort of mind meld on the unconscious Spock. She has removed her sensor net dress.</td></tr>

<tr id="L319"><td><a href="#L319">319</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Unless Miranda can look down into his mind and turn it outward to us, we will lose Spock.</td></tr>

<tr id="L320"><td><a href="#L320">320</a></td><td>KIRK:  (pacing) Vulcan mind techniques. They seem so untrustworthy now that Spock's life is at stake.</td></tr>

<tr id="L321"><td><a href="#L321">321</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Her knowledge of them may be the only thing that could save Spock's sanity, perhaps even his life.</td></tr>

<tr id="L322"><td><a href="#L322">322</a></td><td>KIRK:  But does she want to? She's been in there so long.</td></tr>

<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>MCCOY:  There's nothing else to be done.</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>KIRK:  She tried to help Marvick. Marvick is dead.</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>MCCOY:  That's different. Marvick loved her.</td></tr>

<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>KIRK:  And Spock is her rival. Is that any better? Even Spock felt the violence of her jealousy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>MCCOY:  But they weren't rivals in love. Jim, you shouldn't go in there.</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>KIRK:  Whatever happens, Bones, don't interfere.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>MIRANDA:  Who is it? Doctor McCoy? Who's there?</td></tr>

